dumb thing like that.

145
00:10:00,958 --> 00:10:05,000
I knew him pretty damn well
and that's not how he was.

146
00:10:08,208 --> 00:10:12,416
He paid me his full attention,
always listening with both ears.

147
00:10:12,500 --> 00:10:13,500
No way!

148
00:10:13,583 --> 00:10:15,125
Hiroshi's not like that!

149
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:22,708
Pipsqueak.

150
00:10:22,791 --> 00:10:27,375
Why's that wretched bimbo been
dragging you across the country?

151
00:10:27,458 --> 00:10:30,791
Do you know something
about Hiroshi?

152
00:10:30,875 --> 00:10:33,583
I think at first that was
what she must've thought.

153
00:10:33,666 --> 00:10:35,291
Just at first?

154
00:10:35,375 --> 00:10:38,583
Yeah, cause I didn't know
anything about him then.

155
00:10:38,666 --> 00:10:40,416
I've never even met him.

156
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:43,625
So, I couldn't really
be much help to her.

157
00:10:43,708 --> 00:10:45,416
Even so she stuck with me.

158
00:10:45,500 --> 00:10:48,291
Then you just been
stringing me along, huh?

159
00:10:48,375 --> 00:10:50,083
Shit, you never even met him?

160
00:10:50,166 --> 00:10:52,166
No, but I know
where to find him.

161
00:10:52,250 --> 00:10:53,708
Yeah, where?

162
00:10:55,250 --> 00:10:56,708
I can't say.

163
00:11:02,375 --> 00:11:04,500
I'll let you in on something.

164
00:11:04,583 --> 00:11:07,250
That cold-ass bitch
is still using you.

165
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:09,916
That's for damn sure.

166
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:11,875
Michiko told me
to believe in her.

167
00:11:11,958 --> 00:11:16,666
And she made me a promise,
that she'd always protect me.

168
00:11:16,750 --> 00:11:19,291
Do you believe in her?

169
00:11:19,375 --> 00:11:20,916
Yes.

170
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:23,375
